course.subject: ELEC
course.name: Professional Development in Engineering Business I
course.description: A compulsory, one year course for students in Electronic Engineering - Entrepreneurship Option, and Electronic Engineering and BBA in General Business Management under the three-year degree only. This course is designed to provide academic advising to students and/or to develop students' communication skills in interacting with the technical and non-technical audiences in their professional careers. Focus is on Engineering Marketing, working with Government Regulation, and Entrepreneurship. Graded P or F.
